and do it with professionalism and pride.

261
00:15:00.025 --> 00:15:03.125
And I just think we need to have a round of applause

262
00:15:03.185 --> 00:15:04.245
for our city staff.

263
00:15:14.305 --> 00:15:18.285
Our South Portland city of nearly 27,000 residents

264
00:15:18.285 --> 00:15:21.325
and more than 1200 businesses is my home.

265
00:15:21.665 --> 00:15:24.965
And I am inspired to serve here at the local level

266
00:15:24.985 --> 00:15:29.765
of government, especially right now in this country.

267
00:15:30.305 --> 00:15:31.685
The local level is

268
00:15:31.685 --> 00:15:34.645
where our voices can most clearly be heard.

269
00:15:35.795 --> 00:15:39.125
Ours is a local community willing to step up, adapt,

270
00:15:39.265 --> 00:15:42.285
and come together even in the most challenging times.

271
00:15:42.825 --> 00:15:45.285
And that's clear from South Portland's history.

272
00:15:46.705 --> 00:15:50.685
Here's a powerful story that historian Seth Goldstein shared

273
00:15:50.685 --> 00:15:53.205
with me recently at the South Portland Historical

274
00:15:53.475 --> 00:15:54.525
Society Museum.

275
00:15:57.065 --> 00:16:00.805
In April of 1942, the residents

276
00:16:00.805 --> 00:16:03.925
of the Cushing's Point neighborhood, the area we now know

277
00:16:03.925 --> 00:16:05.925
as our beloved bug light park,

278
00:16:06.765 --> 00:16:08.805
received letters from the federal government

279
00:16:09.835 --> 00:16:11.645
with limited advance warning.

280
00:16:11.855 --> 00:16:16.805
Those letters gave them just nine days to leave their homes

281
00:16:17.225 --> 00:16:20.525
so the shipyard could expand to support the war effort.

282
00:16:22.265 --> 00:16:25.445
Can you imagine being given just nine days for that?

283
00:16:26.775 --> 00:16:29.485
Those families had lived there for generations.

284
00:16:29.975 --> 00:16:32.965
Their lives and memories were rooted in that neighborhood

285
00:16:33.505 --> 00:16:34.805
and it was unfair.

286
00:16:35.865 --> 00:16:39.045
And yet it came at a time when people across the country

287
00:16:39.045 --> 00:16:43.405
were making sacrifices, planting victory gardens,

288
00:16:44.195 --> 00:16:47.365
rationing gasoline, salvaging metal,

289
00:16:47.505 --> 00:16:50.565
and believing deeply in a shared purpose.

290
00:16:51.065 --> 00:16:52.925
At a time of instability

291
00:16:53.025 --> 00:16:56.805
and understandable fear, the families

292
00:16:56.805 --> 00:16:59.005
of Cushing's Point gathered their strength,

293
00:17:00.205 --> 00:17:03.605
accepted compensation that could never replace what was lost

294
00:17:04.065 --> 00:17:06.245
and made their sacrifice with courage.

295
00:17:07.095 --> 00:17:11.445
Those ordinary South Portlanders mobilized to help the world

296
00:17:12.045 --> 00:17:13.285
confront a grave threat.

297
00:17:15.055 --> 00:17:19.505
That story tells us something. South Portlanders show up.

298
00:17:20.305 --> 00:17:24.065
We innovate, we help our neighbors, we work together.

299
00:17:24.405 --> 00:17:28.945
And I have seen that firsthand serving on our school board.

300
00:17:29.145 --> 00:17:31.825
I watched residents from every part of the city work

301
00:17:31.825 --> 00:17:33.265
through tough discussions

302
00:17:33.765 --> 00:17:36.225
to support building a beautiful new middle school

303
00:17:36.565 --> 00:17:40.465
and incredible investment in our children and our future.

304
00:17:42.055 --> 00:17:44.825
Just this year came another generational investment.

305
00:17:45.095 --> 00:17:47.465
When two volunteer led committees,

306
00:17:47.965 --> 00:17:49.485
our conservation committee

307
00:17:49.825 --> 00:17:53.485
and our open space committee, helped our city purchase

308
00:17:53.505 --> 00:17:56.165
and begin to preserve nearly 40 acres

309
00:17:56.225 --> 00:17:59.845
of land near Hinkley Park for public trails

310
00:17:59.945 --> 00:18:02.525
and wildlife conservation and education.

311
00:18:03.815 --> 00:18:06.285
South Portland today is also the kind of city

312
00:18:06.285 --> 00:18:10.365
that helped open the new Preble Street Food Security hub on

313
00:18:10.365 --> 00:18:14.085
our city's west side in its kitchens on Darling Avenue,

314
00:18:14.445 --> 00:18:16.365
I was amazed to learn that staff

315
00:18:16.385 --> 00:18:20.325
and volunteers can prepare up to 10,000 meals a day

316
00:18:20.905 --> 00:18:24.045
and store 50,000 meals to respond to hunger

317
00:18:24.045 --> 00:18:26.325
and emergencies anywhere in Maine.

318
00:18:27.415 --> 00:18:31.485
We're a community where every winter a group of adults

319
00:18:31.585 --> 00:18:35.365
and teenagers makes sure older residents have buckets

320
00:18:35.365 --> 00:18:37.645
of sand delivered to their doorsteps

321
00:18:37.905 --> 00:18:40.165
to help prevent falls on ice and snow.

322
00:18:40.435 --> 00:18:44.205
That is not a federal program and it doesn't make headlines,

323
00:18:44.625 --> 00:18:47.685
but it's neighbors seeing a need and filling it.

324
00:18:49.265 --> 00:18:52.685
And South Portland is a city that welcomes immigrants

325
00:18:52.705 --> 00:18:56.845
who have come here to raise families, educate children,

326
00:18:57.635 --> 00:19:00.605
open businesses, and build prosperous lives

327
00:19:00.625 --> 00:19:03.805
and communities just as immigrants

328
00:19:03.865 --> 00:19:07.045
to America have done for generations.

329
00:19:09.505 --> 00:19:13.365
Now, looking ahead, I believe South Portland's generous,

330
00:19:13.415 --> 00:19:17.605
brave, and bold history can guide us today's challenges,

331
00:19:17.635 --> 00:19:21.245
climate resilience, housing land use the health of our air

332
00:19:21.445 --> 00:19:24.205
and water, and more require knowledge

333
00:19:24.345 --> 00:19:27.925
and courage, creativity and collaboration.

334
00:19:29.825 --> 00:19:30.845
We are in a moment

335
00:19:30.895 --> 00:19:34.445
where South Portland neighbors can help shape South Portland

336
00:19:34.885 --> 00:19:37.805
decisions that will have long lasting impact.

