759
00:52:23.785 --> 00:52:26.285
Do you remember me? I knew the voice.

760
00:52:27.185 --> 00:52:30.565
It took me back in time. More than 40 years.

761
00:52:32.505 --> 00:52:34.825
I looked up and yes, it was Louise Moore.

762
00:52:35.525 --> 00:52:39.265
She was my student at Sawyer School in 1978.

763
00:52:40.365 --> 00:52:42.225
She had come to my home in Saco.

764
00:52:42.665 --> 00:52:44.905
I took her to the beach, had a barbecue with friends.

765
00:52:45.205 --> 00:52:46.585
She remembered all of it.

766
00:52:47.285 --> 00:52:49.185
It had made a difference in her life.

767
00:52:49.925 --> 00:52:51.945
And here she was making a difference in

768
00:52:52.015 --> 00:52:53.745
mine, remembering me.

769
00:52:54.935 --> 00:52:56.585
Some things never change.

770
00:52:58.905 --> 00:53:00.745
I remember the first time I,

771
00:53:06.705 --> 00:53:08.365
The first time I buried a student,

772
00:53:09.365 --> 00:53:11.085
I was teaching at South Portland High School.

773
00:53:11.705 --> 00:53:15.845
Sherry had just graduated a car accident. Tragic.

774
00:53:17.345 --> 00:53:20.325
We stood at the cemetery with about 20 students

775
00:53:20.385 --> 00:53:21.405
who didn't know what to do,

776
00:53:21.665 --> 00:53:25.205
but they weren't ready to go home to leave her there alone.

777
00:53:26.185 --> 00:53:28.285
