Too many drug overdoses, mental health.

783
00:53:43.465 --> 00:53:46.605
Too much to say. Some things must change.

784
00:53:48.375 --> 00:53:51.355
All of us are running around with a sign around our neck

785
00:53:51.355 --> 00:53:52.675
that asks, am I needed?

786
00:53:53.095 --> 00:53:55.635
And the answer is yes, we're all needed.

787
00:53:56.135 --> 00:53:58.515
And finding out how to make a difference is as simple

788
00:53:58.515 --> 00:54:00.955
as looking up saying yes.

789
00:54:02.025 --> 00:54:03.835
When I was teaching at SMCC,

790
00:54:03.915 --> 00:54:06.875
I had a young man from Afghanistan, rasa.

791
00:54:07.695 --> 00:54:10.395
He told me he graduated from Ola Beach High School.

792
00:54:11.515 --> 00:54:12.715
I graduated from there.

793
00:54:12.835 --> 00:54:15.475
I told him, he then proceeded to tell me

794
00:54:15.475 --> 00:54:17.755
that his senior year, his parents got an

795
00:54:17.755 --> 00:54:18.915
apartment in South Portland.

796
00:54:19.015 --> 00:54:20.395
But he didn't want to leave.

797
00:54:21.135 --> 00:54:22.875
He wanted to graduate with his friends.

798
00:54:23.275 --> 00:54:26.755
A place he knew after already having lost so much.

799
00:54:28.655 --> 00:54:30.395
Ms. Sandy was the school secretary.

800
00:54:30.535 --> 00:54:31.955
He said she and her husband,

801
00:54:32.135 --> 00:54:34.075
Mr. George, let me live with them.

802
00:54:34.095 --> 00:54:37.555
My last year. He told me funny stories about his first time

803
00:54:37.555 --> 00:54:41.195
living with a dog and about how she cooked the meat.

804
00:54:41.255 --> 00:54:42.635
So rare he couldn't eat it.

805
00:54:43.975 --> 00:54:45.075
You need to invite her

806
00:54:45.075 --> 00:54:47.075
to hear your sacred story at City Hall.

807
00:54:47.235 --> 00:54:51.955
I said, and he did. And she came and I met her.

808
00:54:53.055 --> 00:54:57.475
But it was not the first time. It was Sandy McSweeney.

809
00:54:57.975 --> 00:54:59.755
We had grown up in the same town,

810
00:55:00.385 --> 00:55:01.915
graduated high school together.

811
00:55:02.715 --> 00:55:04.845
Imagine our lives interconnected.

812
00:55:05.875 --> 00:55:07.645
Some things should not change.

813
00:55:09.225 --> 00:55:12.965
In 2014, I was on an agricultural trip

814
00:55:13.105 --> 00:55:14.605
and we were in Warren in Maine.

815
00:55:15.055 --> 00:55:19.165
There was a man giving us a tour of his farm about my age.

816
00:55:19.945 --> 00:55:23.885
And suddenly I looked up to see a sign that read Spear Farm.

817
00:55:25.855 --> 00:55:28.355
Was your mother's name Edna by any chance?

818
00:55:29.115 --> 00:55:33.285
I asked him when the crowd broke up. Yes it was.

819
00:55:33.425 --> 00:55:37.205
He answered. How did you know? I was stunned.

820
00:55:37.725 --> 00:55:39.605
I couldn't believe what I was about to say

821
00:55:40.235 --> 00:55:44.925
because I said my dad answered an ad in the Boston Globe

822
00:55:44.985 --> 00:55:46.045
in 1940.

823
00:55:47.185 --> 00:55:49.765
He was 16 years old and he came here

824
00:55:49.785 --> 00:55:52.005
and worked as a farm hand for your mom and dad.

825
00:55:52.835 --> 00:55:54.765
It's because of that experience

826
00:55:54.765 --> 00:55:57.125
that he moved his family from Boston to Maine

827
00:55:57.125 --> 00:55:59.565
after the war in 1951,

828
00:56:01.355 --> 00:56:03.765
they came back to this farm for their honeymoon.

829
00:56:04.285 --> 00:56:07.605
I have pictures of it. My mother didn't know what hit her.

830
00:56:07.625 --> 00:56:09.445
She made us laugh when she would say she was

831
00:56:09.445 --> 00:56:10.805
constipated for two weeks.

832
00:56:11.415 --> 00:56:13.725
She'd never seen an outhouse in her life.

833
00:56:14.885 --> 00:56:16.965
I told him the two of us laughed.

834
00:56:17.945 --> 00:56:19.045
The world is small

835
00:56:19.545 --> 00:56:21.445
and if you just take a minute to talk

836
00:56:21.445 --> 00:56:25.085
to someone you don't know, reach out and offer to help.

837
00:56:26.065 --> 00:56:30.085
You'll see how small it really is. Loss is hard.

838
00:56:31.205 --> 00:56:34.255
Starting over is hard. Change is hard.

839
00:56:35.825 --> 00:56:38.835
Just recently I met Father Leopold from Burundi at a

840
00:56:38.835 --> 00:56:39.875
wedding I officiated.

841
00:56:40.495 --> 00:56:41.795
He is a Catholic priest

842
00:56:41.895 --> 00:56:43.915
who started an orphanage in his country.

843
00:56:44.535 --> 00:56:46.155
We met, we talked,

844
00:56:47.595 --> 00:56:50.035
I consider myself a Catholic in recovery.

845
00:56:51.095 --> 00:56:53.675
But my concerns with the Catholic church do not take

846
00:56:53.675 --> 00:56:55.275
precedent over hungry children.

847
00:56:56.235 --> 00:56:58.155
Children who've lost their parents to HIV

848
00:56:58.155 --> 00:56:59.195
or other tragedies.

849
00:56:59.895 --> 00:57:02.795
It does not dominate over the needs of these kids.

850
00:57:03.655 --> 00:57:05.995
So I found a suitcase in my attic, filled it

851
00:57:05.995 --> 00:57:08.955
with children's books, holiday decorations, and a donation.

852
00:57:10.415 --> 00:57:13.475
And again, I was conscious of my privilege.

853
00:57:14.465 --> 00:57:17.755
Rebecca Oliver was my student more than 10 years ago

854
00:57:18.785 --> 00:57:20.005
at the community college.

855
00:57:20.785 --> 00:57:23.045
She just texted me on Friday night to say,

856
00:57:23.185 --> 00:57:25.645
and I quote, you were the jumpstart

857
00:57:25.705 --> 00:57:29.165
to realizing I was worthwhile and I could fight back

858
00:57:29.225 --> 00:57:30.565
and demand I was equal.

859
00:57:31.625 --> 00:57:36.505
I cried. Education is not just about reading, writing

860
00:57:36.725 --> 00:57:37.785
and arithmetic.

861
00:57:38.535 --> 00:57:42.425
It's much more. There are people in our community

862
00:57:42.605 --> 00:57:46.225
who are hungry, alone, lost,

863
00:57:47.615 --> 00:57:49.415
unhoused, confused.

864
00:57:50.225 --> 00:57:51.735
There are people new to our city.

865
00:57:52.155 --> 00:57:56.135
Not sure where to turn, who to trust, how the system works.

866
00:57:56.725 --> 00:57:58.935
Suffering in many ways, much of the time.

867
00:57:59.825 --> 00:58:02.795
Many of my friends like those here tonight.

868
00:58:03.605 --> 00:58:06.865
We must remember there is a power inequity.

869
00:58:07.485 --> 00:58:10.625
And we need to ask, is this the change we want?

870
00:58:11.965 --> 00:58:13.105
I'm a cat lover

871
00:58:13.685 --> 00:58:17.345
and I was reading about room eight, the name of the cat

872
00:58:17.485 --> 00:58:20.545
who lived in a schoolhouse for more than 16 years.

873
00:58:21.605 --> 00:58:24.945
In the writeup it said, and I quote, schools

874
00:58:25.125 --> 00:58:28.985
or communities built on routine, kindness and belonging.

875
00:58:29.295 --> 00:58:32.225
Because every day, hundreds of people show up

876
00:58:32.245 --> 00:58:35.145
to the same place, see the same faces

877
00:58:35.805 --> 00:58:37.945
and following the same rhythms.

878
00:58:38.965 --> 00:58:42.735
Room eight wanted that he wanted to belong somewhere.

879
00:58:43.155 --> 00:58:46.775
So he chose a school and the school chose him back.

880
00:58:47.595 --> 00:58:50.495
He taught routine, showing up every day matters.

881
00:58:51.195 --> 00:58:54.735
He taught responsibility. Someone had to feed him.

882
00:58:55.075 --> 00:58:58.535
Notice when he was hurt, make sure he got home safely.

883
00:59:00.315 --> 00:59:01.535
He taught acceptance.

884
00:59:01.915 --> 00:59:04.735
He had no invitation, no official role,

885
00:59:05.435 --> 00:59:07.255
no purpose except to be himself.

886
00:59:07.755 --> 00:59:08.895
And the door stayed open.

887
00:59:09.555 --> 00:59:13.215
And most of all, he taught that belonging isn't given.

888
00:59:13.645 --> 00:59:18.005
It's created by returning, by trusting,

889
00:59:18.545 --> 00:59:22.885
by being welcomed, by showing up day after day, year

890
00:59:22.885 --> 00:59:27.285
after year, until you become part of the story, end

891
00:59:27.285 --> 00:59:28.645
of the quote from that story.

892
00:59:29.265 --> 00:59:32.285
And 70 years later, people still remember,

893
00:59:32.685 --> 00:59:34.615
roommate, look up.

894
00:59:35.445 --> 00:59:39.265
Our neighbors need us. The stranger on the bus needs us.

895
00:59:40.285 --> 00:59:41.705
Our school youth need us.

896
00:59:43.205 --> 00:59:46.955
My friends who spoke to you tonight, they need us.

897
00:59:48.555 --> 00:59:52.245
They need us to remember their faces, hear their voices,

898
00:59:52.785 --> 00:59:53.885
and listen to their words.

899
00:59:53.885 --> 00:59:57.345
Because it matters. They matter.

900
00:59:58.355 --> 00:59:59.455
And we need them.

901
01:00:00.195 --> 01:00:02.895
We need them to teach us about the needs of all children,

902
01:00:03.545 --> 01:00:05.655
about kindness, openness,

903
01:00:05.755 --> 01:00:10.215
and welcoming others about differences, about how

904
01:00:10.215 --> 01:00:12.215
to live in a community with an open mind

905
01:00:13.035 --> 01:00:14.975
and about how to change this world.

906
01:00:15.945 --> 01:00:17.235
This is education too.

907
01:00:18.875 --> 01:00:21.835
I can tell you that the Somalis make the best Samsa,

908
01:00:22.335 --> 01:00:26.035
the Iraqis, the best doma, the randee, the best.

909
01:00:26.305 --> 01:00:30.675
Sobe, the Cambodians, the best noodles, the angolans,

910
01:00:30.675 --> 01:00:34.915
the best tilapia and the Iranians, the best rice.

911
01:00:36.395 --> 01:00:37.435
I have tried it all,

912
01:00:38.175 --> 01:00:41.075
but my friends have given me more than that.

913
01:00:42.615 --> 01:00:44.455
I have learned about true loss

914
01:00:44.755 --> 01:00:47.135
and suffering, about forgiveness,

915
01:00:48.105 --> 01:00:50.575
about equity, about change.

916
01:00:50.715 --> 01:00:51.975
And it has opened my eyes.

917
01:00:53.075 --> 01:00:55.735
Please remember that even in small ways,

918
01:00:56.715 --> 01:01:00.175
we all have a chance to make a difference, to educate

919
01:01:00.595 --> 01:01:01.775
and be educated.

920
01:01:02.555 --> 01:01:06.615
We can all change. We need to create good change.

921
01:01:07.795 --> 01:01:10.635
The right change. Charan,

922
01:01:14.445 --> 01:01:14.665
Aun,

923
01:01:15.705 --> 01:01:20.155
obrigado, Tasha.

924
01:01:20.315 --> 01:01:21.955
K. Thank you.

925
01:01:36.455 --> 01:01:39.755
Uh, thank you very much for coming tonight and for staying

926
01:01:40.095 --> 01:01:43.795
and for listening, um, and for being attentive

927
01:01:43.895 --> 01:01:44.915
and responsive.

928
01:01:45.175 --> 01:01:48.715
Um, I appreciate everyone being here

929
01:01:48.775 --> 01:01:51.315
and I look forward to the next year.

930
01:01:51.935 --> 01:01:56.235
Um, I look forward to looking out at this audience

931
01:01:56.255 --> 01:01:58.875
and not seeing empty chairs, um,

932
01:01:59.095 --> 01:02:01.275
but seeing the look of difference

933
01:02:01.375 --> 01:02:02.675
and the look of acceptance.

934
01:02:03.535 --> 01:02:05.475
Um, and so I thank you

935
01:02:05.475 --> 01:02:07.355
and I will accept a motion to adjourn.

936
01:02:10.245 --> 01:02:11.545
Oh, somebody, uh,

937
01:02:11.865 --> 01:02:13.545
actually you need to say something, Daniel.

938
01:02:14.585 --> 01:02:16.065
I thought I was seconding. No.

939
01:02:16.065 --> 01:02:17.865
Um, I moved for the inaugural address

940
01:02:17.925 --> 01:02:20.445
to be, uh, spread on the record. Seconded.

941
01:02:21.355 --> 01:02:26.085
Okay. And all those in favor? Okay. And that's unanimous.

942
01:02:26.505 --> 01:02:29.085
And now a motion to adjourn. Move to adjourn.

943
01:02:29.115 --> 01:02:31.925
Move to adjourn by, uh, member Dowling.

944
01:02:32.185 --> 01:02:33.925
And seconded by member Feller.

945
01:02:34.145 --> 01:02:35.725
All those in favor of adjournment

946
01:02:37.315 --> 01:02:39.575
and we are hereby adjourn.

947
01:02:39.575 --> 01:02:40.575
Thank you very much.

948
01:02:49.255 --> 01:02:53.295
I think we have to give it. Likewise. Congratulations.
